{
	// Emit config for the entwurf-bridge MCP server (0.12.1 C — install fix).
	//
	// WHY THIS EXISTS: Node's `--experimental-strip-types` REFUSES `.ts` files
	// under `node_modules` (ERR_UNSUPPORTED_NODE_MODULES_TYPE_STRIPPING). So the
	// 0.12.0 launcher (`node --experimental-strip-types src/index.ts`) works from a
	// dev clone but breaks the moment the package is installed under node_modules
	// (every npm/pnpm consumer). This config tsc-EMITS the bridge boot closure to a
	// plain-JS tree (`dist/`) that boots with vanilla `node` from anywhere. start.sh
	// runs dist/ when its path is under node_modules (installed) and runs the
	// strip-types src/ otherwise (dev clone).
	//
	// FENCE NOTE: the bridge graph is the SAME `.ts`-extension fence the root
	// tsconfig excludes (root is emit-capable and can't allow `.ts` imports). This
	// config pairs `allowImportingTsExtensions` with `rewriteRelativeImportExtensions`
	// (TS 5.7+) instead of `noEmit`, so emitted JS references `.js` paths, including
	// the lazy `await import("./entwurf-preflight.ts")` → `./entwurf-preflight.js`.
	// That dynamic import stays dynamic in the output, so the eager boot closure
	// remains pi-free (check-entwurf-bridge-pi-free) while the owned-outcome resume
	// branch still lazy-loads the pi-backed preflight. This is an EMIT pass, not a
	// typecheck pass — the noEmit typecheck fence (scripts/tsconfig.json) is
	// untouched, so every `.ts` is still typechecked by exactly one `tsc --noEmit`.
	"extends": "../../tsconfig.json",
	"compilerOptions": {
		"allowImportingTsExtensions": true,
		"rewriteRelativeImportExtensions": true,
		"noEmit": false,
		"declaration": false,
		"sourceMap": false,
		"outDir": "./dist",
		"rootDir": "../.."
	},
	// Clear the root `exclude` (it filters out every `.ts`-extension lib file the
	// bridge graph needs). Only node_modules must stay excluded.
	"exclude": ["../../node_modules"],
	// The bridge boot entry (+ the dependency-free protocol.js it reaches via an
	// explicit `.js` import) PLUS the doctor's store-scan helper. tsc auto-follows
	// the import graph — STATIC imports AND the lazy
	// `await import("./entwurf-preflight.ts")` — and emits exactly that closure,
	// nothing more (the pi-lane-only acp/* stays out of the tarball).
	//
	// WHY store-doctor rides THIS build: meta-bridge-doctor.sh's full store scan
	// must run from an INSTALLED package (under node_modules, where strip-types is
	// refused) — the same node_modules boundary start.sh crosses. Its only repo
	// import is pi-extensions/lib/meta-session.ts, which the bridge graph ALREADY
	// emits here, so it adds ONE leaf JS (dist/scripts/meta-bridge-store-doctor.js)
	// and ZERO new deps. It is NOT in index.ts's boot closure, so
	// check-entwurf-bridge-pi-free (which walks the index eager closure) is unaffected.
	//
	// WHY meta-bridge-hook rides THIS build (0.12.5): the SessionStart/UserPromptSubmit
	// plugin hook ran as raw `.ts` (`node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/meta-bridge-hook.ts`).
	// Under an installed marketplace source below node_modules that is
	// ERR_UNSUPPORTED_NODE_MODULES_TYPE_STRIPPING — the SAME strip-types fence
	// start.sh (0.12.1) and the store-doctor (0.12.4) already cross by shipping JS.
	// At 0.12.5 this was the last known `.ts`-at-runtime surface; emitting it here
	// closed that release's set (installer copies dist JS when installed, keeps
	// `.ts` for a dev clone). Its only repo import is meta-session.ts, ALREADY emitted for the
	// store-doctor, so this adds ONE leaf JS (dist/pi-extensions/meta-bridge-hook.js)
	// and ZERO new deps. It is a plugin hook, never in index.ts's boot closure, so
	// check-entwurf-bridge-pi-free is unaffected.
	//
	// WHY agy-imprint rides THIS build (0.12.7): the npm bin resolves to
	// scripts/agy-imprint.sh under node_modules. Running its raw .ts there hits the
	// same ERR_UNSUPPORTED_NODE_MODULES_TYPE_STRIPPING fence. Emit the hook leaf as
	// dist/scripts/agy-imprint.js; the stable bin chooses it only when installed and
	// keeps transparent strip-types source execution in a dev clone.
	//
	// WHY the three OPERATOR commands ride this build (0.12.7): `entwurf` dispatches
	// them through run.sh, whose REPO_DIR is under node_modules once installed — so
	// they hit the same fence the imprint hook did, and shipped dead. They are not
	// dev gates: doctor-pi-provider is the pi-ownership verdict, new-session-id is
	// the operator alias that mints a garden citizen (docs/setup-clean-host.md tells
	// operators to run it from the installed bin), and meta-bridge-prune is the store
	// maintenance verb. check-*/smoke-* stay OUT on purpose — they are dev-clone-only
	// and run_ts refuses them under an installed package rather than emitting 70+
	// gate leaves into the tarball.
	"include": [
		"./src/index.ts",
		"../../protocol.js",
		"../../scripts/meta-bridge-store-doctor.ts",
		"../../scripts/agy-imprint.ts",
		"../../scripts/doctor-pi-provider.ts",
		"../../scripts/new-session-id.ts",
		"../../scripts/meta-bridge-prune.ts",
		"../../pi-extensions/meta-bridge-hook.ts"
	]
}
